name: Applied-Data-Science-with-Python--University-of-Michigan-Specialization-
description: The 5 courses in this University of Michigan specialization introduce learners to data science through the python programming language. This skills-based specialization is intended for learners who have a basic python or programming background, and want to apply statistical, machine learning, information visualization, and text analysis techniques to gain new insight into their data. In the final course, students will work on real-world data analysis projects, building a portfolio which showcases their work while at the same time helping real clients gain a better understanding of their data.
